			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">About the <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Clock_rate">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Clock_rate</a><!-- m --> article...<br />Here are some signals typed-up from pictures seen on an analog scope:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PAL Vblank Start Timing<br />&nbsp; Line&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;--Line238--&gt;&lt;--Line239--&gt;&lt;--Line240--&gt;&lt;--Line241--&gt;&lt;--Line242--&gt;<br />&nbsp; /NMI&nbsp; &nbsp;---------------------------------------__________________________<br />&nbsp; Video: PPPPPPPPP-_C-PPPPPPPPP-_C-----------_C-----------_C-----------_C-<br /><br />PAL Vblank Middle Timing<br />&nbsp; Line&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;--Line268--&gt;&lt;--Line269--&gt;&lt;--Line270--&gt;&lt;--Line271--&gt;&lt;--Line272--&gt;<br />&nbsp; /NMI&nbsp; &nbsp;_________________________________________________________________<br />&nbsp; Video: ----------_C-----------____________-____________-____________-_C-<br /><br />PAL Vblank End Timing<br />&nbsp; Line&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;--Line310--&gt;&lt;--Line311--&gt;&lt;--Line000--&gt;&lt;--Line001--&gt;&lt;--Line002--&gt;<br />&nbsp; /NMI&nbsp; &nbsp;_____________----------------------------------------------------<br />&nbsp; Video: ----------_C-----------_C-----------_C-PPPPPPPPP-_C-PPPPPPPPP-_C-<br /><br />Whereas<br />For Video: P=Picture, -=Blank, _=Sync, C=ColorBurst<br /></div><br />/NMI is toggled on &amp; off at the begin of the line (after the ending &quot;-_C-&quot; blanking part of the previous line).<br />VSYNC is toggled at HSYNC, while active, it changes the &quot;-_C-&quot; part to &quot;-___&quot;, and also changes the next lines &quot;picture&quot; part from &quot;---&quot; to &quot;___&quot;.<br /><br />What you can see in the above drawings (and what is probably also mentioned on many other places) is that PAL outputs only 239 picture lines, not 240 (as said in the wiki article; unless I've somehow misread that, too). <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /> So a PAL frame should consist of these 312 lines:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; 1 line pre-rendering<br />&nbsp; 239 lines rendering<br />&nbsp; 1 line post-rendering<br />&nbsp; 70 lines vblank<br />&nbsp; 1 line post-blank<br /></div><br />I guess NTSC should be the same, but with only 20 lines vblank... unless NTSC outputs more or less than 239 picture lines?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

