						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">nocash wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">On tepple's NTSC NES, that &quot;reset period&quot; lasts until around 261 lines after reset (=until END of vblank), that's different as in the wiki article; which says around 241 lines after reset (=until BEGIN of vblank).</div><br /><br />If the Reset/Power on time was 261/262 scanlines long, Time Lord wouldn't work.  That game is sloppily coded, and never clears frame IRQs after it disables them.  If the reset timing is inaccurate, it will get a frame IRQ and will never clear it.  This messes up the game after it begins the first level.<br />The game works if the first frame begins near scanline 0 or prerender line, and fails if the first frame begins near scanline 240 or vblank line.</div>

					
