					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">the dot is indeed skipped even when only sprites are on (I tested this personally even</div><br />Good to know! Thanks.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I don't know exactly what a &quot;curved line&quot; would look like</div><br />Somehow like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; Vertical&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Curved&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Bold<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;xxxxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; xxxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; xxxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;xxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;xxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;xxx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; XX&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Xx<br /></div><br />Is the NTSC NES doing that? If yes, it might be best-visible if you can tweak the TV set to show the top-most scanlines (via VHOLD or VSIZE knobs or so).<br /><br />---<br /><br />Yup, with the missing dot, there's an integer number of NTSC color cycles (3.5xxMHz) per 2 frames. So the &quot;dot crawl&quot; is just jumping back-and-forth (which will be seen as flimmering, rather than actual crawling). Without the missing dot, there should be some visible crawl (where the dots are constantly wandering back) (or maybe vice-versa: constantly forth).<br /><br />On PAL it's different, there's an integer number of PAL color cycles (4.xxMHz) per EVERY frame. So there's no crawl, and even no flimmering. Which, I think doesn't actually look any good. The composite artifacts are &quot;perfectly&quot; visible on PAL. With a blurry back-and-forth effect (as on NTSC), the PAL picture might have looked much smoother.</div>

